eds to be restarted periodically\n\n## Accomplished\n\n✅ Project structure (client/server folders)\n✅ Python Flask backend with SQLite database\n✅ JWT authentication system\n✅ 80 cards seeded (Pokémon, Magic, One Piece, Dragon Ball - 20 each)\n✅ Pack opening system with gacha probabilities and pity\n✅ Collection display with filters\n✅ Deck builder (create, edit, delete decks)\n✅ Marketplace auctions\n✅ Daily missions system\n✅ Chat system\n✅ Profile with achievements\n✅ React frontend with inline styles (Tailwind wasn't working)\n\n## In Progress\n\n- Adding new backend endpoints for:\n  - Tournament system\n  - Player stats tracking\n  - Welcome pack for new players\n  - Card selling\n  - NPC daily deals\n  - Simple duel engine\n\n## Relevant Files\n\n```\n/home/chier/\n├── server/\n│   ├── index.py          # Flask backend (currently has syntax errors)\n│   └── another_world.db  # SQLite database\n└── client/\n    ├── src/\n    │   ├── App.jsx      # Main React component with all pages\n    │   ├── index.css     # Basic CSS\n    │   └── main.jsx     # Entry point\n    ├── index.html\n    └── package.json\n```\n\n## Current Issue\n\nThe backend `index.py` has a syntax error on line 1021-1022 in the `get_npc_deals` function. The SQL query string building is malformed. Need to fix this and restart the server.\n\n## Next Steps\n\n1. Fix syntax error in `/home/chier/server/index.py` \n2. Restart the Flask server\n3. Update the React frontend to use the new API endpoints (welcome pack, sell cards, tournaments, NPC deals, duel)\n4. Test all features work together\n5. Make UI improvements for \"official launch\""}]},{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Continue if you have next steps, or stop and ask for clarification if you are unsure how to proceed."}]},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking what we did so far, and I've been given a detailed summary of the project history. Let me look at the current state of the pro